WEBVTT

00:32.575 --> 00:35.494
(Person whistling tune)

00:54.305 --> 00:57.183
(Whistling continues intermittently)

01:15.284 --> 01:17.703
(Soft drums music intro playing)

01:21.916 --> 01:24.335
(Cranes whirring and clanking)

01:35.554 --> 01:37.723
(Soft drums music continues)

01:42.895 --> 01:45.314
(Intermittent whistling continues)

02:02.331 --> 02:03.833
(Soft creaking)

02:06.127 --> 02:08.545
(Suspenseful music rising)

02:21.559 --> 02:22.852
(Music ends in flourish)

02:25.187 --> 02:27.732
(Suspenseful jazz music playing)

02:33.154 --> 02:35.573
(Fingers snapping rhythmically)

02:42.872 --> 02:44.248
(Boy whistles)

02:46.584 --> 02:47.710
(Chuckles)

02:58.304 --> 03:00.306
(Whistling)

03:00.389 --> 03:01.390
Jets!

03:26.290 --> 03:28.584
(Discordant jazz music playing)

03:29.543 --> 03:30.628
(Jets member whistles)

03:30.711 --> 03:31.712
(Metal clinks)

03:32.213 --> 03:33.506
(Tyres screech)

03:33.589 --> 03:34.757
(Jets member whistles)

03:42.348 --> 03:43.349
(Snaps fingers)

03:46.185 --> 03:47.311
Woman: Hey, hey!

03:57.363 --> 03:59.782
(Melodious jazz music playing)

04:16.589 --> 04:18.843
(Melodious jazz music continues)

04:30.187 --> 04:32.398
(People chattering in Spanish)

04:35.025 --> 04:37.403
(Suspenseful jazz music playing)

04:49.415 --> 04:50.499
Come on.

04:54.003 --> 04:56.547
(Waltzy jazz music playing)

05:00.926 --> 05:02.595
- Ha!
- (Man speaking Spanish)

05:02.678 --> 05:04.972
(Waltzy jazz music continues)

05:12.313 --> 05:14.315
(Shouting in Spanish)

05:18.402 --> 05:20.154
(Continues shouting in Spanish)

05:20.779 --> 05:22.281
Jets: Yeah! Come on, come on!

05:22.364 --> 05:23.657
(Whooping)

05:26.452 --> 05:28.454
(Dramatic music playing)

05:31.207 --> 05:32.333
(Music ends)

05:37.171 --> 05:38.172
Beat it.

05:38.255 --> 05:39.524
(Suspenseful jazz music playing)

05:39.548 --> 05:40.883
(Metal clinks)

05:49.183 --> 05:51.810
- (Frantic jazz music playing)
- (Jets clamouring)

05:55.898 --> 05:57.149
Jets member: Oh, yeah!

05:57.233 --> 05:59.735
(Men speaking Spanish)

06:01.987 --> 06:04.114
(Jets clamouring and whooping)

06:09.203 --> 06:10.871
(Whistles)

06:12.873 --> 06:14.875
(All clamouring)

06:22.967 --> 06:25.219
(Frantic jazz music continues)

06:35.521 --> 06:36.522
Boy: Hey!

06:37.940 --> 06:39.650
Hey, you! Come on!

06:44.196 --> 06:45.614
(All grunting)

06:53.872 --> 06:55.082
(Man laughs)

07:00.421 --> 07:02.256
(All grunting)

07:03.424 --> 07:04.633
(Man laughs)

07:07.886 --> 07:10.180
(Shouts) Jets!

07:15.352 --> 07:16.632
Jets member: Come on, baby John!

07:16.770 --> 07:18.230
(Baby John screaming)

07:21.150 --> 07:22.776
(All grunting)

07:32.911 --> 07:33.912
(Whistle blows)

07:34.455 --> 07:35.873
(Brakes screech)

07:35.956 --> 07:37.958
(Frantic jazz music continues)

07:38.792 --> 07:40.461
(Whistle blowing)

07:40.544 --> 07:42.880
Officer: Alright now, all you separate!

07:44.840 --> 07:47.134
Separate! Separate!

07:47.801 --> 07:49.654
You're driving me to my grave,
ya pack of jackals.

07:49.678 --> 07:50.947
Watch yourself, sergeant krupke,

07:50.971 --> 07:52.032
you're gonna inflame your asthma,

07:52.056 --> 07:53.376
- shouting like that.
- (Laughter)

07:53.557 --> 07:55.976
Why don't you leave
the Puerto Ricans alone, riff?

07:56.060 --> 07:58.228
Christ almighty. And you lot,

07:59.188 --> 08:00.397
you're in New York now.

08:00.481 --> 08:01.961
You got a problem, you call the cops.

08:02.024 --> 08:03.901
Youse can't play
at being cops yourselves.

08:03.984 --> 08:06.862
Pero we call the cops,
you show up and arrest us!

08:06.945 --> 08:08.906
You're never around
when these hijueputas

08:08.989 --> 08:10.741
mess up our stores and our streets.

08:10.824 --> 08:12.785
See, I get confused
when you say "our streets,"

08:12.868 --> 08:14.620
seeing how these streets
are ours by right

08:14.703 --> 08:16.330
- of being born here, amigo.
- The jets!

08:16.413 --> 08:18.582
(All arguing indistinctly)

08:18.666 --> 08:20.709
How many times do I gotta tell you,
Bernardo?

08:20.793 --> 08:22.086
I don't speak spic.

08:22.169 --> 08:23.796
- (Squabbhng)
- Krupke: Hey, hey!

08:23.879 --> 08:24.939
That's enough! That's enough!

08:24.963 --> 08:27.758
- (Whistle blowing)
- Come on! Break it up!

08:32.054 --> 08:34.932
Jesus wept, baby John.

08:35.599 --> 08:37.851
Who did that to your ear?

08:41.730 --> 08:43.732
Which one of them nailed you?

08:50.614 --> 08:52.616
Who cracked your head open, hombre?

08:52.700 --> 08:54.535
- (Speaks Spanish)
- In English.

08:56.328 --> 08:58.831
Same guy who nailed your ear, maybe?

09:01.208 --> 09:03.377
Maybe. I don't remember.

09:03.460 --> 09:05.045
I realise if any of you helps me out,

09:05.129 --> 09:07.339
you might spoil your chance
to murder each other

09:07.423 --> 09:09.925
over control of this earthly paradise.

09:10.008 --> 09:12.136
The jets control it and you know it.

09:12.594 --> 09:13.595
Uh-huh, yeah,

09:13.679 --> 09:15.514
but, golly gee, Balkan, not according

09:15.597 --> 09:17.933
to the New York City committee
for slum clearance,

09:18.016 --> 09:20.352
which has decided
to pull this whole hellmouth

09:20.436 --> 09:21.603
down to the bedrock,

09:21.687 --> 09:23.355
and you're in the way.

09:23.814 --> 09:26.483
Aah! (Shuddering)

09:28.527 --> 09:29.820
(Whistles)

09:31.864 --> 09:33.949
Nice reflexes, muchacho.

09:34.116 --> 09:35.993
So, any day now,

09:36.076 --> 09:37.536
all of you are gonna be evicted.

09:37.619 --> 09:39.997
You'll have to "vamoose,"
as we say in Spanish.

09:40.080 --> 09:41.331
We're not relocating.

09:41.415 --> 09:42.541
(Man speaks Spanish)

09:42.624 --> 09:43.959
We have rights.

09:44.376 --> 09:47.421
Rights, huh? Where are they?

09:47.504 --> 09:48.815
- (Bernardo growls)
- (Speaks Spanish)

09:48.839 --> 09:51.175
You back down, Bernardo.
Don't be stupid.

09:54.511 --> 09:57.097
Some night, muchacho,

09:58.140 --> 09:59.808
maybe you'll get to see me fight.

09:59.892 --> 10:02.311
'Course, you'll have to leave
your gun at home, lieutenant.

10:04.563 --> 10:07.608
Evict yourself off my crime scene,
Bernardo.

10:09.610 --> 10:10.861
Vamos.

10:16.033 --> 10:18.035
(Jets taunting)

10:18.243 --> 10:19.828
Jets member: Chick, chick, chick.

10:19.912 --> 10:22.706
(Jets member 2 whistles tauntingly)

10:22.790 --> 10:24.225
Jets member: Chickie, chickie, chickie.

10:24.249 --> 10:26.251
(Singing in Spanish)

10:30.798 --> 10:33.091
- (Jets snickering)
- A boxer and a singer.

10:33.175 --> 10:34.611
Jets member 3: Get a load of this guy.

10:34.635 --> 10:37.137
(Continues singing in Spanish)

10:39.515 --> 10:41.058
(Jets laughing)

10:41.141 --> 10:43.393
(All singing)

10:48.982 --> 10:50.818
You want me to book
the whole bunch of you?

10:50.901 --> 10:52.903
Keep up the serenade and see what...

10:52.986 --> 10:54.988
(Singing continues)

10:57.407 --> 10:59.785
[Viva Puerto Rico iibre!

10:59.868 --> 11:02.955
I am ordering you clowns to disperse!

11:05.833 --> 11:06.834
Now!

11:06.917 --> 11:09.044
(All continue singing)

11:18.220 --> 11:19.972
(Crowd cheering)

11:23.100 --> 11:24.852
We're outnumbered, boys.

11:24.935 --> 11:26.895
Thousands more are on their way,

11:26.979 --> 11:28.188
and once they're here,

11:28.272 --> 11:30.816
they pop out kids like crazy.
Am I right?

11:31.358 --> 11:33.485
Tell me which one of them
nailed baby John's ear

11:33.569 --> 11:35.237
and I'll put him out of circulation.

11:35.779 --> 11:36.905
Work with me, fellas.

11:36.989 --> 11:38.466
Or they're gonna drive you
off your turf.

11:38.490 --> 11:40.409
You said it was
the slum clearance committee

11:40.492 --> 11:41.535
that was driving us off,

11:41.618 --> 11:43.036
now it's the prs.

11:43.120 --> 11:45.706
You gotta get your story straight,
lieutenant schrank.

11:45.789 --> 11:47.541
We're very impressionable.

11:48.542 --> 11:50.460
Most of the white guys
who grew up in this slum

11:50.544 --> 11:51.670
climbed their way out of it.

11:51.753 --> 11:54.089
Irish, Italian, Jews.

11:54.172 --> 11:56.425
Nowadays, their descendants
live in nice houses

11:56.508 --> 11:58.135
and drive nice cars

11:58.218 --> 12:01.054
and date nice girls you'd want to marry.

12:01.138 --> 12:04.349
Your dads or your granddads stayed put,

12:04.975 --> 12:07.519
drinking and knocking up
some local piece

12:07.603 --> 12:09.313
who gave birth to you.

12:10.439 --> 12:13.942
The last of the
can't-make-it caucasians.

12:14.109 --> 12:17.237
What's a gang without its terrain,
its turf?

12:17.321 --> 12:19.072
You're a month or two away
from finding out,

12:19.156 --> 12:20.991
one step ahead of the wrecking ball.

12:21.074 --> 12:22.534
And in this uncertain world,

12:22.618 --> 12:25.621
the only thing you can count on is me.

12:25.704 --> 12:27.205
I'm here to keep the civil peace

12:27.289 --> 12:28.624
until the last building falls.

12:28.707 --> 12:30.000
And if you boys make trouble

12:30.083 --> 12:32.044
on my turf, riff, hand to heart,

12:32.127 --> 12:34.004
you're headed to an upstate prison cell

12:34.087 --> 12:35.964
for a very long time.

12:37.299 --> 12:38.842
By the time you get out,

12:40.177 --> 12:43.138
this will be a shiny new neighbourhood
of rich people

12:43.221 --> 12:45.390
in beautiful apartments

12:46.016 --> 12:50.312
with puerto rican doormen
to chase trash like you away.

12:54.733 --> 12:55.734
Wait!

12:58.612 --> 13:00.656
I got a question for you, lieutenant.

13:03.700 --> 13:05.494
How tall did you used to be before you,

13:05.577 --> 13:06.912
you know, "schrank"?

13:06.995 --> 13:08.497
(Jets laughing)

13:09.247 --> 13:10.666
Come on, sergeant, ride with me.

13:10.749 --> 13:12.042
Long as I know you, riff,

13:12.125 --> 13:14.086
you ain't had the sense,
god gave a pigeon.

13:17.214 --> 13:19.216
Riff: Come here, let's see what he done.

13:20.884 --> 13:21.885
Come on.

13:23.512 --> 13:24.906
Well, that's gonna scar, buddy boy.

13:24.930 --> 13:27.641
- You think so? (Chuckles)
- Frankenstein time.

13:27.724 --> 13:29.184
They can't make us up and leave.

13:29.267 --> 13:30.268
We're here, ain't we?

13:30.352 --> 13:32.813
American citizens,
which them spics ain't!

13:32.896 --> 13:34.231
Them they can chase off, not us.

13:34.314 --> 13:35.416
Puerto Ricans are Americans,

13:35.440 --> 13:36.960
- you ignoramus.
- Ah, go eat a green banana!

13:36.984 --> 13:39.003
Puerto Rico's like a state,
ain't it? So, deez is right...

13:39.027 --> 13:40.088
Baby John: No, it's something else.

13:40.112 --> 13:41.339
Jets member: There are only 48 states,

13:41.363 --> 13:42.590
- ya dead battery.
- What do you know?

13:42.614 --> 13:43.949
- (Laughter)
- Whatever they are,

13:44.032 --> 13:46.660
citizens or who gives a fart,
what we know is...

13:46.743 --> 13:48.412
Jets member 2: They ain't us.

13:48.495 --> 13:50.789
So, spill it, krazy Kat,
what are you thinking?

13:50.872 --> 13:52.249
(Metal clinks)

13:52.332 --> 13:55.293
I'm thinking it's past time
for a rumble.

13:55.877 --> 13:58.547
For a all-in, all-out, once-and-for-all,

13:58.630 --> 14:00.882
winner-takes-all, high-noon-shootout-

14:00.966 --> 14:03.006
- at-the-o.k. Corral rumble!
- (All shout excitedly)

14:03.051 --> 14:05.095
Balkan: Wild blue yonder! About time!

14:05.178 --> 14:06.572
We do 'em like we done
the Egyptian kings.

14:06.596 --> 14:08.076
- And the emeralds.
- And the bishops.

14:08.265 --> 14:09.701
Alright, so Tony and me
will sit down with...

14:09.725 --> 14:10.994
- Jets member: Tony?
- Yeah, Tony.

14:11.018 --> 14:12.120
Jets member 2:
What's this got to do with him?

14:12.144 --> 14:13.454
He ain't stood with us
once since he got out.

14:13.478 --> 14:15.480
He's on parole.
He's gotta be careful, is all.

14:15.564 --> 14:16.749
He cannot be running around...

14:16.773 --> 14:18.233
Tony's done with the jets, riff.

14:18.316 --> 14:20.444
He ain't done with the jets.
Like that's even a thing!

14:20.527 --> 14:21.879
You cannot be done with this family.

14:21.903 --> 14:24.281
Maybe it wasn't a thing before,
but now, riff?

14:24.698 --> 14:26.199
The lieutenant's right.

14:26.283 --> 14:28.118
What are the jets
if we got no territory?

14:28.201 --> 14:29.429
- Jets member: That's right!
- All: Yeah.

14:29.453 --> 14:32.080
Schrank doesn't know
his ass from his elbow.

14:32.664 --> 14:33.707
Look,

14:33.790 --> 14:36.460
Tony and me started the jets

14:36.543 --> 14:37.895
cause none of us would even be here

14:37.919 --> 14:39.212
if it wasn't for all of us.

14:39.588 --> 14:41.348
- And all you know it.
- (Jazz music playing)

14:41.423 --> 14:44.301
(Singing) When you're a jet
you're a jet all the way

14:44.384 --> 14:47.637
from your first cigarette
to your last dyin' day

14:48.221 --> 14:50.974
when you're a jet
if the spit hits the fan

14:51.058 --> 14:54.644
you got brothers around
you're a family man

14:54.728 --> 14:56.063
you're never alone

14:56.354 --> 14:57.981
you're never disconnected

14:58.690 --> 15:00.400
you're home with your own

15:00.484 --> 15:02.027
when company's expected

15:02.110 --> 15:03.862
you're well-protected

15:03.945 --> 15:06.823
then you are set with a capital j

15:06.907 --> 15:10.077
which you'll never forget
till they cart you away

15:10.160 --> 15:11.161
when you're a jet

15:11.244 --> 15:13.705
- (tyres screech rhythmically)
- You stay a

15:14.081 --> 15:16.917
-jet -(Cars horns honking)

15:18.585 --> 15:20.879
So, meet Tony and me
at the dog days dance

15:20.962 --> 15:21.963
at the gym tonight.

15:22.047 --> 15:24.216
We can't rumble at the gym,
it'll be lousy with cops!

15:24.299 --> 15:25.651
And maybe we've had enough trouble

15:25.675 --> 15:26.903
with the Puerto Ricans for one day?

15:26.927 --> 15:29.262
Relax. It's a social mixer.

15:29.346 --> 15:31.848
So we'll mix until the time's right

15:31.932 --> 15:33.892
to fix the rumble for tomorrow night.

15:34.184 --> 15:36.436
Be there 10:00 pm, punctual-like,

15:36.520 --> 15:38.271
dressed to kill, walking tall!

15:38.355 --> 15:40.148
We always walk tall! We're jets!

15:40.315 --> 15:41.775
The greatest.

15:42.109 --> 15:44.861
(Singing) When you're a jet
you're the top cat in town

15:44.945 --> 15:48.740
you're the gold-medal kid
with the heavyweight crown

15:48.824 --> 15:49.908
when you're a jet

15:49.991 --> 15:53.286
you're the swingin'est thing
little boy, you're a man

15:53.370 --> 15:55.330
jets: Little man you're a king

15:55.413 --> 15:56.748
riff: The jets are in gear

15:56.832 --> 15:59.084
our cylinders are clickin'

15:59.584 --> 16:01.128
the sharks'll steer clear

16:01.211 --> 16:04.214
jets: Cause every
puerto rican's a lousy chicken

16:04.714 --> 16:07.425
here come the jets
like a bat out of hell

16:07.509 --> 16:10.720
someone gets in our way
someone don't feel so well

16:11.346 --> 16:14.099
here come the jets
little world, step aside

16:14.182 --> 16:15.851
better go underground

16:15.934 --> 16:17.477
better run, better hide

16:17.978 --> 16:21.523
we 're drawin' the line
so keep your noses hidden

16:22.107 --> 16:25.277
we 're hangin' a sign
says "visitors forbidden"

16:25.360 --> 16:26.945
and we ain't kiddin'

16:27.195 --> 16:30.115
jets: Here come the jets, yeah
and we're gonna beat

16:30.198 --> 16:33.410
every last buggin' gang
on the whole buggin' street

16:33.493 --> 16:34.828
on the whole

16:34.911 --> 16:37.205
ever mother-lo vin'

16:37.289 --> 16:42.836
street

16:42.919 --> 16:44.462
- yeah!
- (Music ends)

16:49.301 --> 16:50.760
- Can.
- Riff: Come on.

16:50.844 --> 16:52.345
Just for an hour, only a little hour.

16:52.429 --> 16:53.722
You used to like dancing.

16:53.805 --> 16:55.557
- No monkeyshines.
- Come on, riff, can.

16:57.225 --> 16:59.853
Christ almighty. You know,
there's dust on everything.

16:59.936 --> 17:00.937
You know, ever since...

17:01.021 --> 17:02.564
Hey, I swear on what's holy,

17:02.647 --> 17:05.483
it is just girls sipping punch
and music...

17:05.567 --> 17:06.794
- And the sharks.
- And the spics.

17:06.818 --> 17:07.962
- And a rumble.
- Which all you gotta do...

17:07.986 --> 17:09.046
You're on your own, pal-o-mine.

17:09.069 --> 17:10.256
Is help me haggle
over the terms of the rumble.

17:10.280 --> 17:11.757
You don't need me helping ya
screw up your life.

17:11.781 --> 17:13.509
You know how I get.
I will start runnin' my mouth.

17:13.532 --> 17:15.410
You... you got command.

17:15.492 --> 17:17.704
You are West Side legendary! And, Tony,

17:17.787 --> 17:21.374
Tony, the jets.
I gave 'em my word you'd show.

17:22.459 --> 17:24.461
- Why would you do that?
- Because...

17:24.961 --> 17:26.296
Because it's a rumble!

17:26.378 --> 17:27.839
We need you if we're going to war.

17:27.923 --> 17:30.759
You can't refuse us now.
And because I know you.

17:31.218 --> 17:32.219
Or I thought I did,

17:32.302 --> 17:33.613
before you got all unlike yourself,

17:33.637 --> 17:35.305
before you went upstate.

17:35.597 --> 17:37.641
Woman: Tony? (Speaks Spanish)

17:37.724 --> 17:39.476
I'm coming!

17:43.271 --> 17:44.540
It's like you're still in prison,

17:44.564 --> 17:46.441
and the old witch is the warden.

17:48.151 --> 17:51.112
She gave me a job and a place to stay.

17:51.196 --> 17:54.282
She's always been there
for me, like nobody else.

17:54.366 --> 17:56.010
- Oh, nobody, huh? Thanks, pal.
- So don't call her...

17:56.034 --> 17:57.094
Thanks a big fat lot. Yeah.

17:57.118 --> 17:59.162
You know I didn't mean you wasn't there.

17:59.246 --> 18:00.747
You was always there.

18:02.958 --> 18:04.417
- Womb to tomb.
- Sperm to worm.

18:04.501 --> 18:07.087
So, come with me to the dance, huh?

18:07.170 --> 18:08.421
Come on.

18:13.593 --> 18:15.220
Is it graziella? That what's eatin' you?

18:15.303 --> 18:16.447
No, it ain't grazie. (Chuckles)

18:16.471 --> 18:17.573
She said that you and she was done.

18:17.597 --> 18:18.658
It's good that
you're keeping her company.

18:18.682 --> 18:19.825
Even before you got locked up, you know?

18:19.849 --> 18:22.227
It's cool. Don't get all
the way you get.

18:23.436 --> 18:27.565
Grazie's a great girl,
and the jets are the greatest.

18:27.649 --> 18:31.069
And you, you're like,
you know, blood to me.

18:37.450 --> 18:39.077
But I'm scared of myself, riff.

18:41.871 --> 18:44.582
What I done to that kid.
What I almost done.

18:44.666 --> 18:46.042
You gotta get over that.

18:46.126 --> 18:47.726
What is the point
in beating yourself up?

18:47.794 --> 18:50.880
I wanna be unlike how I was.

18:50.964 --> 18:52.757
Cause I was disappearing down a sewer

18:52.841 --> 18:53.985
and taking you and everything with me.

18:54.009 --> 18:55.927
- Woman: Tony, you coming?
- Yeah, he heard ya!

18:56.011 --> 18:58.847
I had time. Lots of it.

